name: Pizza Hut
directions: Straight to the back when you walk in, there’s a single stall to the right and a single stall right at the very back

name: GBK
directions:
Downstairs is a single accessible toilet (possibly with baby changing)
Upstairs are 5 single stall/room toilets, 3 female, 2 male (if I remember correctly).
comment:
The upstairs toilets are just 5 stall sized rooms accessed from a corridor desperate to the restaurant floor. While each is speratly gendered, being single stall rooms with standard toilets, there would be no one to question you.
Might have to be a customer, but I've used them without when it's quiet and they're fine.

name: Wagamas
directions: Ground floor, at the back of the restaurant.
comment: Not sure about the toilets upstairs, but the downstairs one is a single stall/room unisex, disabled, baby-changing toilets. Probably have to be a customer to use.

name: Lina’s Diner and Bar
comment: Single stall gender neutral

name: Ministry of Coffee
directions: Ungendered single stall

name: 4205 Belfort Rd, Jacksonville, FL 32216, USA
directions: In hospital, every floor, look for signs
comment: Single stalls, one toilet and sink in each, clean, NOT GENDERED ~ Jay (Agender)

name: St Lukes Ap, Jacksonville, FL 32216, USA
directions: In hospital, look for signs
comment:
Single stalls, one toilet and sink in each, NOT GENDERED! - Jay (Agender)

Have a good day/night

name: St Lukes Ap, Jacksonville, FL 32216, USA
directions: In hospital
comment: Single stalls, one toilet and a sink each. NOT GENDER -Jay (Agender)

name: Chuy's
directions: When you walk in the door head straight, you'll see a sign that says 'Restoom'.
comment: You don't have to be a paying customer.

name: Nation's

comment: For customers only, perhaps just by a drink

name: Pret A Manger
directions: Upstairs

name: Center for Civil and Human Rights
directions: Third floor

name: 5218 Silverberry Dr, Corpus Christi, TX 78417, USA
directions: In between the Willy Wonka machine and the water fountains
comment: You have to be in the movie area (like watching a movie because you have to get pass the ticket person)

name: Territorial Statehouse State Park Museum
directions: Two gender-neutral, single-stall restrooms inside the museum building. Two multi-stall, gender-specific restrooms on park grounds, one operated by Fillmore City and the other by Territorial Statehouse State Park.
comment: Museum has an admission fee, but no charge just to use restrooms. The one furthest from the entrance door has a changing table, both are accessible. Public restrooms outside on the west end of the park have changing tables in both men and women sides.

name: Cinemark Fayette Mall
directions: Almost directly behind the ticket taker, between 2 theaters
comment: This is a unisex Family restroom. Since it is in the theater hallway, you will probably need a ticket.

name: Museum of Ancient Life
directions: In the lobby (free space)

name: Museum of Natural Curiosity
directions: In the lobby and in the paid admission areas of the Museum.

name: Katzingers Delicatessen
directions: Back right side of the eating area past the drink station. There are 2 available. Signs indicate
comment: The place is small, but there are shopping/ordering/seating areas. The restrooms are by the kitchen area.

name: DMV
directions: Next to desk

name: Ross dress for Less
directions: It is on the left right by the dressing room

name: El Huerto Superfood Bar
directions: Right in the back

name: Loch coffee
directions: Back of the Café down the hall on the left. Two separate bathroom

name: Automatic Toilet (Oxford Road/Wilson Road)
directions: Directly on the Oxford Road, just down from the Army Reserve Center
comment: Automatic street convenience. Payment required.

name: Halfords Autocenter
directions: Inside customer waiting room/reception
comment: Paying customers only.

name: Pret A Manger (The Oracle)
directions: Off the seating area behind the counter.
comment: Paying customers only. 3 unisex single cubicles off a shared corridor. One fully accessible.

name: Pret A Manger
directions: At the back
comment: Customers only. Unisex accessible single cubicle for all customers.

name: Lake Harriet United Methodist Church
directions: Basement labled "unisex" bathroom
comment:
In a Christian Church that is very accepting
Services (don't feel pressured to come)
Sunday: 9:00, 11:11, (summer) 10:00
Wednesday: 6:30 (half hour service) pizza starts at about 5:30

name: Brandner Gardens
directions: Community garden building.  Single stall unisex bathroom

name: Starbucks
directions:
Depending on where you come in, from the parking lot or from the street. Parking lot: if you walk in it’s on your right hand side. you can avoid all people and don’t need to pass workers. 
If you’re coming in from Main st.: it’s ALL the way in the back and you have to pass by all the workers. 
To get to the parking lot: If you’re coming from west make a left on Greene St., if you’re coming from the east make a right on Greene St., there will be a parking lot with a Chase Bank on your right hand side, that is a community parking lot. from there, you will find the back entrance to the Starbucks that is accessible to all patrons.
comment: Very nice and won’t ask questions:)

name: Starbucks
directions: walk in and it’s on your right hand side where people wait on line.
comment: i go in all the time and just pee and nothing happens. everyone is super nice!

name: Little Nook Cafe
directions: As soon as you walk in, it’s straight ahead in between the opening of the two counters.
comment: they’re really nice and have vegan foods there and mac and cheese pizza !! it’s all really good and they have LGBT nights and stuff. oh they also close at like 3am !

name: Ellensbrook
directions: Follow Ellensbrook Road to the left when it forks.   Park in the car park and follow the path towards the old house.   The toilets are on your left.
comment: Available 24/7.  Be aware they're composting toilets and don't flush.   They don't smell,  but no water is available,  so no handwashing facilities.

name: Margaret River Tourist Information Center
directions: In the back of the Tourist Information Center.   Parking is available behind the Center or in the street.
comment: Only available when the Center is open for business.

name: Margaret River Leisure Center
directions: Enter the front door of the Leisure Center and continue past the desk, straight towards the basketball court.   The rest rooms are on your right.
comment: There is no charge to use the toilet.   It is only available when the Center is open.

name: Pioneer Park
directions: Park in Cowaramup townsite or there is plenty of parking in Memorial Drive.   The toilets are behind the large shed.
comment: The toilets are large enough to be wheelchair accessible but the doors are quite heavy and awkward.  There is a bitumen path to the doors.  The area is very quiet and safe.

name: Walker Library
comment:
One of the restrooms is accessible, single seat. 
Hours: https://www.hclib.org/about/locations/walker

name: Chabot Space and Science Center
directions: On the bottom floor by the “touch the sun” exhibit.
comment: Really cool place, I’d recommend checking it out!!

name: Panera bread
directions: In the back just past the fountain drink area.

name: WaBa Grill
directions: Straight in the back as soon as you walk in. Can’t miss it.
comment: Customers only, but the food is great so highly recommend

name: Jackson School of Geosciences
directions: Take the elevator to the 4th floor and turn in the direction of "after hours book dropoff". It will be on your right.
comment: There is no automatic door button.

name: Engineering Education and Research Center
directions: It's on the 0th floor (2nd is the ground floor). It is in the space with the gray brick that says James J. And Miriam B. Mulva Conference Center and Auditorium, right next to the gender of restrooms. The room is called 0.8T3.

name: Robert Lee Moore Hall
directions: Go into the Kuehne Library and take a left towards the stairs. Walk up one flight and the restroom is on that floor. You have to go around some bookshelves to get to it but it is visible from the stairs.

name: Student Activity Center
directions: On the first floor, in between Zen and the BoA ATM,  there is a little hallway type area and the bathroom should be the first door on your left.
comment: The restroom is very large but the door is not automatic and must be opened with the handle

name: Circle K
comment: Gendered single stall. No one made eye contact with my wife and eye which is good enough for me since we're in the middle of nowhere. We did go in together, though, and someone was very very pushy to get in.

name: Caffe Nero
directions: Walk through the entrance and just walk straight to the back wall

name: Crepe One
directions: Walk in, make a right, it's there
comment: There's a sign on the door that says this, but you can't go in without being a customer. You're also apparently not allowed to ask

name: North Seattle College
directions: Under the stairs near the student cafe “Grove”
comment: Specifically denotes gender nutural use

name: Natural Physicians
comment: For patients of clinic

name: 7 feathers rest area
directions: Roadside rest area.

name: Lancaster University
directions: Various locales across campus - the Library, the Learning Zone, several cafes (including Costa and Subway), all self-contained, gender-neutral spaces.

name: Spoke wine bar
comment: Two single person rest rooms.

name: Downtown Summerlin
street: 1980 Festival Plaza Dr, Las Vegas, NV 89135
directions: By the Earl of Sandwich's and SkinnyFats. There is a corridor and at the end there is a bathroom for anyone.
comment: There are no restrictions, it's for whoever.

name: Pawleys Island Tavern
directions: Only restroom is a single unisex, and quite large.
comment: For restaurant patrons. The food is excellent, though!

name: Counseling Services of Vienna
directions: On the second floor, turn right off getting the elevator and it will be one of the corner doors.
comment: Might need a key from one of the offices but not sure.

name: Amazon Spheres
directions: 3rd floor has 100% gender neutral private stalls.
comment: Must be amazon employee or signed in guest.

name: Starbucks
comment: Need code for bathroom

name: Cafe Deia
directions: In back on the left, single gender neutral bathroom
comment: Patrons only. Friendly staff, but not the most trans aware.

name: Made in Belfast
directions: Back of the restaurant, it’s labeled and hard to miss
comment: Very safe restrooms, stalls are like an individual room

name: Rian
comment: Act like your waiting for an order, then ask the barista for the restroom code. You can go out the back door in order to avoid awkward eye contact when you leave.

name: Home Depot
directions: Left entrance on the left wall.

name: Raley’s
directions: All the way down aisle 15 in the back on the right

name: Rubio's
directions: Two single stalls

name: Two Boots Pizza
comment: have to be paying customers, vegan and vegetarian options, drinks are $3 or less

name: JRI/Boston Glass
directions: Boston GLASS is around the corner of JRI, where there is a parking lot between buildings, there are picnic benches outside of GLASS. JRI should also have unisex bathrooms.
comment: Local queer organization with drop in space for youth (up to 25 years old), safe sex materials and all types of free services and events.

name: Robbins Center -
directions: 8th floor
comment: Must be a client receiving transgender voice therapy

name: Herbert Lewis cafe
directions: Second floor, up the stairs directly opposite the entrance

name: Starbucks on Boise ave at Apple
directions: Hang a right after entering door closest to Rite Aid. Like all Starbucks bathrooms, this is a gender-neutral, single room, locking restroom.
comment: Best to be a paying customer although employees would probably be cool if you didn’t purchase. Ethically, it’s up to you.

name: Victoria Conference Centre
directions: Second floor, left side of big entrance
comment: It may depend on what is going on if you can use it or not (if you’re not planning on going) p.s I messed up name 1st submitting this whoops

name: Mar
directions: Second floor on the end near the painting. Left side of the big entrance
comment: Depends on the event is on if you’re going to use it. I was there for the Comic Con and you had to have a ticket.

name: Sidebar
directions: In the back

name: Starbucks
directions: It’s in the back of the shop.
comment: Not very clean. They usually don’t care if u just go to the bathroom but i️ would get something just in case!

name: Mia
directions: Located on second floor inbetween the yoga room and the main excercise room.
comment: You must be a member to use the facilities on this floor including this restroom. However there are more gender neutral restrooms on the first floor near the men's locker room.

name: Neville House, Bracknell RG12, UK
directions: Top floor of library
comment: Have to be a paying customer of cafe. Quite small, but unisex

name: Walmart
directions: Where the electronics, movies, and video games are there are restrooms. One says Family restroom and it is a single stall. It is safe.

name: Yorkshire MESMAC York Office
directions: From Museum Gardens (Marygate), head across the road to a small ally (Marygate Lane).  Go past a bollard in the middle of the alley and Yorkshire MESMAC is on the right.  The doors and window frames are all purple.
comment: You need to ring to enter and this is the home of York LGBT Forum!

name: Fresno Cory College
directions: In the Music/Speech Building 2nd floor, there’s a single use bathroom that is gender neutral/handicapped shared.
comment: This is the one bathroom I have been told by college faculty and staff that is a “safe space” for me to use the restroom.

name: UMM Library
directions: At junction between Library and Torrey Hall
comment: Two gender neutral bathrooms, private area, very safe college campus
